    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p> <p>Grate the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skin on)&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the grated<strong> potato</strong> to a pot of boiling water and bring to the boil over a high heat with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p> <p>Once boiling, cook the potato for 5 min, then drain and leave to steam-dry in a sieve&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the<strong> leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span><strong> butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p> <p>Once melted, add the <strong>leeks</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the softened leeks and cook for 1 min, stirring it with a wooden spoon</p> <p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and whisk for 3-5 min into a smooth sauce&nbsp;</p> <p>Meanwhile, peel and grate the <strong>garlic</strong> into the sauce and add the <strong>bay leaf</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the skin from the <strong>mackerel </strong>and discard it, then break the mackerel up into different sized pieces, some small flakes and some larger chunks</p> <p>Grate the <strong>cheddar</strong></p> <p>Once thickened, remove the&nbsp;sauce from the heat, and mix in the drained<strong> potato</strong>, <strong>mackerel</strong> and <strong>cheddar</strong> with a pinch of<strong>&nbsp;salt </strong>and<strong> pepper&nbsp;</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove&nbsp;the<strong> bay leaf</strong> and transfer the mixture to an oven-proof dish (or individual ones)&nbsp;</p> <p>Scatter the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> over&nbsp;</p> <p>Put the gratin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> on a baking tray and into the oven for 10 min or until bubbling and golden on top&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear the&nbsp;<strong>little gems </strong>roughly<strong>&nbsp;</strong>and add them to a bowl to serve</p> <p>Chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p> <p>For the dressing, combine the <strong>mustard</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chives</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Dress the salad just before serving&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-leek-gratin/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once golden, serve the gratin with the salad to the side (it will be very hot!)</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
